# Design handoff bundles — build inputs, not site content
*handoff*.zip

# Source video kept out of the repo.
# hero.mp4 is the original 4K clip, superseded by hero1.mp4 and no longer
# used to generate assets/frames/. Regenerate frames with:
#   ffmpeg -i assets/hero1.mp4 \
#     -vf "deband=1thr=0.02:2thr=0.02:3thr=0.02:range=16:blur=1,gradfun=strength=1.2:radius=16" \
#     -c:v libwebp -q:v 85 -compression_level 6 -start_number 0 assets/frames/%04d.webp
assets/hero.mp4

# Master video files for the AI viral ad case study. The web-encoded copies
# live in assets/work/ai-viral-ad/videos/ (1280px, crf 24) and are committed;
# these masters stay local. Re-encode with:
#   ffmpeg -i <master> -vf "scale='min(1280,iw)':-2" -c:v libx264 -crf 24 \
#     -preset slow -pix_fmt yuv420p -c:a aac -b:a 128k -movflags +faststart out.mp4
assets/work/ai-viral-ad/*.mp4
!assets/work/ai-viral-ad/videos/

